## THE AI AGENT ARCHITECTURE\
\
Five AI agents power the platform:\
\
### Agent 1: The Matchmaker\
- Processes intake questionnaire data into squad assignments\
- Matching factors: timezone compatibility, goal type diversity (business/personal/spiritual), personality balance (driven + reflective), experience level\
- Runs every sprint cycle (6 weeks) to form new squads or reshuffle\
- Improves over time using retention and outcome data\
\
### Agent 2: The Sprint Facilitator\
- Runs the complete 6-week sprint cadence automatically\
- Monday: Goal-setting prompts \uc0\u8594  collects declarations \u8594  shares with squad\
- Wednesday: Status check prompts (Green/Yellow/Red) \uc0\u8594  surfaces blockers \u8594  facilitates peer support\
- Friday: Reflection facilitation \uc0\u8594  win celebration \u8594  learning extraction\
- Week 3: Dip Intervention (motivation reset, goal adjustment amnesty)\
- Week 6: Retrospective \uc0\u8594  squad continuation vote \u8594  reshuffle logistics\
\
### Agent 3: The Personal Coach\
- 1-on-1 AI conversations for goal refinement, obstacle analysis, mindset support\
- Full context of user's sprint history, completion rates, patterns\
- Personalized insights: "You've missed Wednesday check-ins 3 sprints in a row \'97 mid-week engagement predicts lower goal completion"\
- Available 24/7 between human check-in touchpoints\
- Distinct from squad interactions \'97 this is private, personal\
\
### Agent 4: The Engagement Guardian\
- Monitors all squad activity for disengagement signals\
- Detects: missed check-ins, declining message length, silent days, goal vagueness\
- Triggers the "Pause Protocol" \'97 empathetic private outreach before the user decides to leave\
- Manages pause/resume flow without disrupting squad dynamics\
- Alerts the founder when a squad is at risk of collapse\
\
### Agent 5: The Analytics Engine\
- Per-user metrics: goal completion rate, attendance, engagement score, streak data\
- Per-squad metrics: squad health score, interaction density, continuation probability\
- Sprint Report Cards at end of each cycle\
- Churn prediction: "This user has a 72% chance of leaving after this sprint"\
- Feeds data back into Matchmaker for improved future compositions\
- Generates founder dashboards for business-level KPIs\
